weather.description: It's mid 90s in COL, which is fun because even in bad hitting weather the elevation makes for good hitting weather... and today we actually have good hitting weather.
Winds are blowing in from center at 10mph.

Heavy rain has faded in to lingering showers. Those lingering showers will eventually fade to nothing. Just enough upstream for a late start or delay, but I expect they play this game, even if it happens in light rain or with a late start.

Storms popped over NY, but quickly cleared. There's a few more upstream drifting towards NYY but my guess would be that it never arrives and this game plays without issue. Late start or a delay is possible, but not the likely outcome.
That same spotty development west of NYY game could potentially make it all the way to NYM, but I have my doubts it ever arrives. Low chance of a delay or late start.
Showers never formed near BOS, should be good to go all night.
Closed roof.
